The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Calcutta, May 18: Tata Motors is likely to announce a salary hike for its employees in 2009-10 on July 1, despite the global economic downturn. The wage hikes wont be as much as the previous years level. But, unlike other companies who have freezed salary hikes this year, we are definitely looking at giving wage increases to our staff, Tata Motors vice-president (human resources) S.J. Tambe said. The increment would be in single digits this year, Tambe added.                            
	 New Delhi, May 18: The government will raise additional Rs 6,000 crore through market borrowings this month, to finance its increasing expenditure, taking its total debt to Rs 2,47,000 crore for the first half of this fiscal. The government has decided to increase the issuance size of the dated securities to Rs 15,000 crore from Rs 12,000 crore in each of the two auctions, from May 15-29.                            
	 New Delhi, May 18: Apollo Tyres has completed the acquisition of the Netherlands-based Vredestein Banden BV for an undisclosed sum from Russias tyre manufacturer AmtelVredestein NV. Apollo Tyres said it had got all regulatory approvals and consent from the Dutch courts to acquire the company.                             
	 Mumbai, May 18: Aditya Birla Nuvo will raise Rs 1,000 crore through the issue of warrants to its promoter group on a preferential basis. The board of directors has decided to issue Rs 1.85 crore warrants to the promoter group on a preferential allotment basis.                            
	 Mumbai, May 18: Manoj Kumar Kohli, CEO and joint managing director of Bharti Airtel, has acquired 80,000 shares for Rs 3.04 crore pursuant to the companys employee stock option scheme. Kohli has bought shares representing 0.004 per cent of the companys stake.                             
	 Chennai, May 18: Madras High Court today set aside an interim injunction restraining TVS from manufacturing and marketing two-wheelers using the twin spark plug internal combustion engine technology.                             
	 New Delhi, May 18: Wheat procurement has touched a new high of 226.93 lakh tonnes this season, surpassing last years record of 226.89 lakh tonnes, according to the latest official figures.                                                                                                                                      
